目錄
Product Code: 10-005Abstract
OVERVIEW

 With recent milestone achievements anharp rise in new techniques, the field of
 genetic analysis has become one of the fastest growing areas of opportunity
 for life science suppliers. Disruptive technological breakthroughs such as
 next generation sequencing and sequencing the human genome have spawneost of
 discoveries in fields like transcriptomics, metagenomics and gene regulation.
 Additionally, as the costs associated with genomic research go down, players
 are entering the market aapid rate.


 Smart life science suppliers are moving quickly to respond to this changing
 market. In our November 2010 report, Genomic Technologies: Market Insights for
 Life Science Suppliers BioInformatics LLC quantifies and characterizes the
 market for genetic analysis including those products use for genome-wide
 association studies (GWAS), copy number variation (CNV) analysis, genotyping
 and techniques such as microarrays, sequencing and real-time PCR. For
 strategic planning purposes, the report includes average lab budgets for
 genetic analysis products and anticipated growth in FY2011, with specific
 breakdowns by geographic region and customer segment. In addition, the report
 estimates market share across different technologies (including microarrays,
 sequencing, real-time PCR etc.) and market share by major suppliers.


 To assist with competitive benchmarking, study respondents are asked to
 indicate preferred brands and rank suppliers on multiple features (i.e., cost,
 data quality, ease-of-use, throughput etc.) This helps identify must-have
 features and unmet needs of current technologies, which illuminates gaps in
 individual vendor offerings and opportunities in the market ahole.
 Additionally, the report delves deeper into microarray and sequencing
 workflows so that suppliers might better understand how researchers are
 employing genetic analysis instruments and consumables.


 Genomic Technologies: Market Insights for Life Science Suppliers provideoadmap
 for genetic analysis product suppliers to help navigatandscape that is poised
 for change - and growth. This analysis was designed to guide suppliers in
 redirecting resources to new areas and markets, and to help refine current
 offerings by making them more responsive to scientists who are already engaged
 in the field of genetic analysis.

OBJECTIVES

 The purpose of this survey is to quantify and characterize the market for
 genetic analysis products, including those for genome-wide association studies
 (GWAS), copy number variation (CNV) analysis, genotyping, and techniques such
 as microarrays, sequencing and real-time PCR. Towards this end, the following
 objectives will be met:


Estimate average laboratories budget for genetianalysis products and
 anticipated growth in FY2011 and FY2012 budgets by geographic region and
 customer segment.
 Generatreakdown oestimated share of the genetic analysis product market by
 technology type (e.g., microarrays, FISH, microscopy, real-time PCR, etc.).
 Identify the major suppliers of genetic analysis productand estimate the
 share of the market.
 Identify those features of current genetic analysitechnologies of greatest
 importance to investigators
 (e.g. speed, read-length, application flexibility, etc).
 Gauge satisfaction with current microarray ansequencing technologies.
 Additional understanding of microarray and sequencinworkflows (e.g., types
 of analysis performed, systems owned and used, and where they conduct the
 analysis).

